Tunde Opalana, Abuja The Peoples Democratic Party Governors Forum (PDPGF) has expressed concern over state of insecurity in the country and its resultant effects on food security and called on President Muhammadu Buhari to declare State of emergency on security mattets. The PDPGF was  very concerned about how farmers are scared to go to their farms for fear of being killed or kidnapped and urges the President to declare a state of emergency on security matters. Rising from a closed door meeting yesterday evening held at the Gombe State Governors Lodge, Asokoro, Abuja with leaders  of the party in attendance , the governors also  agreed to apoint the Bayelsa Statev governor, Seriake Dickson as the new chairman of PDPGF. Dickson who read the resolution of the meeting said “following a consensus agreement, Governor Henry Seriake Dickson of Bayelsa State has been elected Chairman of the PDPGF to succeed “Governor Ibrahim Dankwambo whose tenure expires by the end of the month$. Though not mentioned, the Daily Times learnt that the PDP governors also ratified their consensus choice for the chairmanship of the Nigeria Governors’ Forum at a meeting of the NGF later held yesterday night. The  PDP governors were to support either  Gov. Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti or  Gov.Nasir el-Rufai of Kaduna as the chairman of NGF following the expiration of  tenure of Governor Suleiman Yari of Zamfara State. At the closed door meeting  were the National Chairman of PDP, Prince Uche Secondus, President of the Senate, Dr. Bukola Saraki, Speaker, House of Representatives, Rt. Hon. Yakubu Dogara and the Vice Presidential candidate of the party in the February 23 Presidential poll, Mr.Peter Obi. States governors present at the meeting include the host, Ibrahim Dakwambo, Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto, Emmanuel Udom of Akwa Ibom, Emmanuel Ortom of Benue, Seriake Dickson of Bayelsa and Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta. Also at the meeting was  Rt. Hon. Emeka Ihedioha , Imo State governor- elect.